main event: A civilian reported an unidentified flying object in Dover, New Jersey on November 11, 1966.
interesting points: The object was reported to have stopped abruptly and moved extremely fast,The observer described the object as a small, fast-moving glowing object about the size of a grapefruit,The object was seen for about 35 seconds and appeared to disappear while a plane passed by,The witness did not attempt to report the incident as it was not deemed significant at the time,The questionnaire includes detailed questions regarding the object's behavior, speed, and visual characteristics.
